<h1>About Us</h1>

<h2>Mission &amp; Vision</h2>
<p>The purposes of the De Pere Sportsmen's Club shall be to promote and stimulate interest in conservation and outdoor sports in the State of Wisconsin and to improve in the use of firearms and archery by the establishment of suitable grounds and range facilities.</p>
<h2>Volunteer Opportunities</h2>
<p>The work of the De Pere Sportsmen's Club cannot be conducted without the assistance of lots of volunteer time. The Club relies on the work of its members to keep the grounds clean and well maintained, to complete special projects, always assure safety on the Club grounds. </p>
<p>Club clean up days are held a various times throughout the year to conduct maintenance and cleaning. Please consider volunteering some time to help with keeping the Club and grounds one of the best. Dates for these events are listed on the calendar elsewhere on this website, announced in the newsletter, and posted on the bulletin boards in the Clubhouse.</p>
<p>The short story is that the Club operates through the efforts of a great number of volunteers, and all members share in the responsibility of assisting in keeping the Club clean, safe, and well-maintained to ensure its use by future generations. Please consider providing some of your time to make this happen.</p>
